{
  "texts": [
    "However, a comprehensive explanation of the sources and diffusion of invasive technologies to explain technological change is a difficult topic due to manifold complex and inter-related factors in the presence of a changing and turbulent environment, such that Wright (1997 Wright (, p. 1562) aptly claims: \"In the world of technological change, bounded rationality is the rule.\"",
    "Trends of invasive technology i at t are analyzed with the following model:",
    "Log 10 y i, t = a + b time + u i, t",
    "Qeios, CC-BY 4.0 • Article, February 29, 2024 Qeios ID: NR1YME • https://doi.org/10.32388/NR1YME 11/35 y t is the number of patents of invasive technologies t = time u t = error term (a = constant; b = coefficient of regression) Note: *** p<0.001; Explanatory variable: time; period is from the starting year of the patent to 2023 (last year available); In round parentheses, the Standard Error.",
    "The F-test is based on the ratio of the variance explained by the model to the unexplained variance."
  ]
}